# ROYAL MASTER DEGREE | SECOND SECTION {{bookmark rm-work-2}}

Note: In this section, H._A. is absent and his station is
   draped in mourning. The lights are dimmed as far as
   practical. The Candidate(s) with C._C. come to the
   door of the Council Room and one of them gives the
   alarm:

Cand: ●●● ●●● ●●
CG: Illustrious King Solomon, there is an alarm at the door
   of the preparation room.
KS: Attend the alarm, and report the cause.
CG: (_Goes to door, gives ●●● ●●● ●●, then opens it._)
   Who comes here?

Note: As this is the first time they are addressed, every
   effort should be made by C._C. to speak each
   candidate's name clearly. {{endnote-ref candidate-names}}

CC: Companion(s) A, B, C, and D who, having been
   regularly Initiated, Passed, and Raised to the Sublime
   Degree of Master Mason, advanced to the Degree of
   Mark Master Mason, inducted into the Oriental Chair as
   [a] Past Master(s), received and acknowledged [a] Most
   Excellent Master(s), and exalted to the Most Sublime
   and August Degree of the Holy Royal Arch, seek[s]
   further light in Masonry by being introduced to the rites
   and honors of a Royal Master.
CG: Companion(s) A, B, C, and D, is it of your own free will
   that you make this request?
Cand: It is.
CG: Companion Conductor of the Council, [is he] (are they)
   duly and truly prepared, worthy and well qualified?
CC: [He is] (They are).
CG: [Has he] (Have they) shown suitable proficiency in the |
   preceding degrees to entitle {him/them} to advancement? <|
CC: [He has] (They have).
CG: By what further rite or benefit [does he] (do they) expect
   to gain admission into this Council of Royal Masters?
CC: The benefit of the pass.
CG: [Has he] (Have they) the pass?

%PAGE
CC: [He has] (They have) it not, I have it for {him/them}.
CG: Give me the pass.

Note: C._C. advanced and whispers the pass (APH) into the
   ear of C._G., then returns to stand with candidate(s).

CG: `Tis well. Wait until the Illustrious Master is informed of
   your request and his answer returned.

Note: C._C. closes door, advances to altar and salutes K._S.

KS: Who caused the alarm?
CG: Companion(s) A, B, C, and D who, having been
   regularly Initiated, Passed, and Raised to the Sublime
   Degree of Master Mason, advanced to the Degree of
   Mark Master Mason, inducted into the Oriental Chair as
   [a] Past Master(s), received and acknowledged [a] Most
   Excellent Master(s), and exalted to the Most
   Sublime and August Degree of the Holy Royal Arch, seek[s]
   further light in Masonry by being introduced to the rites
   and honors of a Royal Master.
KS: Is it of {his/their} own free will that {he/they} make[s]
   this request?
CG: It is.
KS: [Is he] (Are they) duly and truly prepared, worthy and
   well qualified?
CG: [He is] (They are).
KS: [Has he] (Have they) shown suitable proficiency in the |
   preceding degrees to entitle {him/them} to advancement? <|
CG: [He has] (They have).
KS: By what further rite or benefit [does he] (do they) expect
   to gain admission into this Council of Royal Masters.
CG: The benefit of the pass.
KS: [Has he] (Have they) the pass?
CG: [He has] (They have) it not, {his/their} conductor has it
   for {him/them}.
KS: Give me the pass.

Note: C._G. whispers the pass without leaving the altar.

KS: `Tis well. Form the Cherubim {{endnote-ref cherubim}} within the
   S._S., then admit and receive the candidate(s) in form.

%PAGE figure
Figure 11.

## ROYAL MASTER DEGREE | Preparing for Reception of Candidates.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/11-rm-preparing-second.png" 26
%SPACE
If there are not enough Cherubim to span from wall to wall with
arms outstretched, it is permissible for the Cherubim to be divided
into two groups, one group spanning from the north edge of the 
floor to the north side of the altar, and the other from the south side
of the altar to the south edge of the floor, instead of being
positioned west of the altar. The Cherubim should all come into
this position facing towards the center of the room (north or south).
Once in place, all Cherubim should turn simultaneously, those on
the north to the west, and those on the south to the east.

%PAGE
Note: C._G. forms Cherubim wall to wall, facing inward,
   after which K._S. gives ● ●, to be taken as a count of
   1 & 2. All perform a Right Face on the mental count
   of 3 & 4, then slowly lift and extend their "wings" to
   span the room from north to south. See Fig. 11.

CG: (_Returns to door and opens it._) It is the order of
   the Illustrious Master that Companion(s) A, B, C
   and D be admitted. Let {him/them} enter.

## RECEPTION OF CANDIDATE(S)

Note: C._C. and candidate(s) enter. C._G. closes the door after <|
   them, then returns to his station. C._C. takes first <|
   candidate's right arm, leading towards Cherubim:

CC: Upon this, your first admission into a Council of Royal
   Masters, I am commanded to receive you beneath the
   extended wings of the Cherubim at the entrance to the
   Holy of Holies, (_Two Cherubim, still facing West tilt
   their "wings" up for C._C. and candidate(s) to pass
   between without being made to stoop. After all
   candidates have passed through—_) which is to teach
   you that the still small voice of Ultimate Truth is best
   nurtured under the balancing protective wings of our
   mind's opposing faculties: the expansive impulse of
   intuitive [[smallcaps]]wisdom[[/smallcaps]], tempered by the long-suffering and
   measured discernment of rational [[smallcaps]]understanding[[/smallcaps]].

## CIRCUMAMBULATION

Note: C._C. and candidate(s) make eight circumambu- |
  lations. K._S. begins reading when C._C. first passes
  the east, and knocks as east is passed again at the
  completion of each circuit. {{endnote-ref solomons-reading}}

KS: And he set the Cherubim within the inner house, and they
   stretched forth the wing of the Cherubim so that the
   wing of the one touched the one wall and the wing of
   the other Cherub touched the other wall, and their wings
   touched one another in the midst of the house. ||
