## ROYAL MASTER DEGREE | Circumambulation of Candidates.
%SPACE
%IMAGE "figures/12-rm-circumambulation.png" 26
%SPACE
Eight circuits are made during the scripture reading. K._S. gives the
prescribed raps with the gavel at the end of each.

A ninth circuit is made in order to conduct the candidate(s) through
the Cherubim to K._S. in the East, for further examination and
instruction, with the Cherubim being dismissed by a rap of the
gavel immediately after C._C. and candidate(s) pass through.

%PAGE
Note: After scripture, C._C. conducts candidate(s) one final
   time clockwise to the east for examination and
   instruction. After they pass under the Cherubim on
   the north, (See Fig. 12), K._S. gives ● which dissolves
   the Cherubim (returning them directly to their
   original seats, retracing the path of their arrival.)
   C._C. and candidate(s) halt in the East and C._C.
   gives an alarm of ●●● ●●● ●●.

KS: Who comes here?
CC: Companion(s) A, B, C, and D who, having been
   regularly Initiated, Passed, and Raised to the Sublime
   Degree of Master Mason, advanced to the Degree of
   Mark Master Mason, inducted into the Oriental Chair as
   [a] Past Master(s), received and acknowledged [a] Most
   Excellent Master(s), and exalted to the Most Sublime
   and August Degree of the Holy Royal Arch, seek[s]
   further light in Masonry by being introduced to the rites
   and honors of a Royal Master.
KS: Companion(s) A, B, C, and D, is it of your own free will
   that you make this request?
Cand: It is.
KS: Companion Conductor of the Council, [is he] (are they)
   duly and truly prepared, worthy and well qualified?
CC: [He is] (They are).
KS: [Has he] (Have they) shown suitable proficiency in |
  the preceding degrees to entitle {him/them} to advancement? <|
CC: [He has] (They have).
KS: By what further rite or benefit [does he] (do they) expect
   to gain this important favor.
CC: The benefit of the pass.
KS: [Has he] (Have they) the pass?
CC: [He has] (They have) it not, I have it for {him/them}.
KS: Give me the pass.

Note: C._C. advances, whispers pass, and returns to floor.

KS: `Tis well. Conduct {him/them} to the Captain of the
   Guard who will teach {him/them} how to approach the
   East as [a] Royal Master(s).

%PAGE

Note: C._C. conducts candidate(s) to the west and speaks
    without making an alarm. (See Fig. 13)

CC: Companion Captain of the Guard, it is the order of
    Illustrious King Solomon that you teach Companion(s)
    A, B, C, and D how to approach the East as [a] Royal
    Master(s).

Note: C._G. comes down and demonstrates with the last |
   candidate, while C._C. assists the other candidate(s). <|

CG: Face the east. Advance o s w y r+ f+, bringing t~ heel o |
   t~ l+ t t~ heel o t~ r+, forming 2 s> of an equilateral △, |
   y b e+. (_Done._) Illustrious King Solomon, Companion(s)
   A, B, C, and D {is/are} in order.
KS: Companion(s), once again you stand before the Sacred
