## INSTRUCTION

KS: (_Descends from dais, approaches from the east as he
   continues:_) You observe me as Illustrious Master of the
   Council, approaching you from the east by the step,
   under the sign of a Royal Master. Royal Masters a> o s |
   w t~ r+ f+, b@ t h o t~ l+ t t~ h o t~ r+, f 2 s> o a e △. This <|
   is the sign of a R._M.  It is made by p@ b h> p d o t o t~ h, <|
   w t~ f> i<, and alludes to the penalty of the obligation.
   Ever remember upon entering or retiring from a Council
   of Royal Masters to advance to the altar and salute the
   Illustrious Master with this sign (_demonstrates again_). |
   _ |
   I will now invest you with the sign of recognition, pass,
   grip and words of a Royal Master. You being
   uninstructed, the Captain of the Guard will answer for
   you. The sign of recognition is made by taking any
   article in hand, passing it to the person you wish to test,
   and with three taps of the foot asking: ● ● ● Do you
   know anything about this?

Note: K._S. passes the charter, a Masonic coin, or some
   other object to candidate.

CG: I d, I k t b@. W+ d y k a i+?
KS: I k t e. W+ i t~ b@?
CG: A. W+ i t~ e?
KS: O.
CG: T~ f+.
KS: T~ l+.
CG: T~ b@.
KS: T~ e. ||
   (_Reclaims object, and takes candidate by the hand_) |
   A. and O. are the principal words of a R._M. Arise.

Note: K._S. steps back & faces H._K._T.  They start to form a |
   L._A., but one of the indispensable 3 being a+, they
   place h> o e o> s>. K._S. pointing to feet says:

KS: W d y s there?
HKT: A b △.
KS: A!
HKT: P H.
KS: "A! P H." is the p w and t> is t~ g o a R._M. (_With |
   the r+ f+ forming two s> of an e △, place b h> o |
   each o> s>._)

Note: K. S. or assistants must demonstrate the grip with
   each candidate during or after this explanation:

KS: We learn from Masonic tradition that the origin of this |
   grip is as follows: S._K._O._I. and H._K._O._T., meeting in the <|
   S._S., shortly after the death of H._A., placed themselves |
   involuntarily in the position to give the M._W., when 
   suddenly, realizing that one of their number was
   wanting, they immediately placed their hands on each
   other's shoulders, and Solomon, pointing down asked,
   "W d y s t?" H._K._O._T replied, "A b △." Both throwing |
   up their arms, Solomon exclaimed, "A!"  H. of T. replied, <|
   "PH."

Note: K._S., H._K._T. & C._G. return to their stations. C._C.
   conducts candidate(s) to the east. (See Fig. 15)

%SPACE 2

## ROYAL MASTER DEGREE | WORKING TOOLS {{bookmark rm-tools}}

KS: The Working Tools of a Royal Master are the Pencil, the
   Compasses, and the Trestle-Board, which were chief
   among the tools employed by our G._M._H._A. ||
   {{endnote-ref rm-tools}}

   The Pencil is a tool used by Operative Masons to
   skillfully draft plans for the instruction and guidance of
   the craft; the compasses are used to determine the limits
   and proportion of its parts with accuracy and precision;
   and the Trestle-board to receive the plans of a master
   architect and convey them to those employed in the
   construction of the building.

   But we as Speculative Masons, are taught to use the
   pencil for the more noble and glorious purpose of
   recording our most worthy and exalted designs upon the the
   Trestle-board which resides in the hearts of our
   Friends and Companions, so that if we die before it has
   been accomplished, our work may be completed if it is
   found within the due bounds set by the Compasses of |
   the Supreme Architect of the Universe.

   Companion Conductor of the Council, conduct our
   companion(s) to a seat for the delivery of the Lecture.

